User explicit request: 'dont hardcode please. all should be automatic your
logic should be in that way'.

REMOVED:
  - The 5-event hardcoded CURATED_EVENTS array (Vedanta / Wipro / Honeywell /
    QXO / Adobe) — institutional-quality but inherently stale, written for
    a specific April 2026 snapshot. No way to keep that fresh without
    manual rewrite per event.
  - Per-company fact tables, EV scenarios, mechanics rows, SoP allocations,
    timing notes, and playbook entries — all hardcoded, all gone.

EVERYTHING ON THE PAGE NOW IS:
  (a) live data pulled from /api/v1/special-situations/feed (refreshes
      every 30 min from 14 RSS sources), or
  (b) algorithmic classification logic (tier scoring + freshness +
      ticker mention count), or
  (c) universal investing rules / pure-math calculators.

ALL SITUATIONS tab — algorithmic tier classification:
  Tier 1 (Hard catalyst):  type ∈ {SPIN, MA, CAP} AND age ≤14d AND
                            ticker count ≥1
  Tier 2 (Watchlist):       age ≤30d, anything else
  Archive:                  >30d (collapsed by default)

  Per-event score (0-100):
    Freshness component (40 max) — TODAY=40, THIS_WEEK=30, RECENT=18, OLDER=5
    Type component (30 max) — SPIN=30, MA=28, CAP=22, TURN=15
    Ticker specificity (20 max) — 7 per ticker, capped at 20
    Source institutional weight (10 max) — Reuters Business=10, BS=9 etc.

  Each row shows: type pill, region flag, ticker chips, freshness badge,
  score, source, headline, description preview, external-link icon.
  Click row = open primary source in new tab.

WHEN TO BUY / SELL — universal investing rules across 4 archetypes
  (Demergers, Tender Buybacks, Open-Market Buybacks, Merger Arb).
  Static reference content — same rules apply to any spin-off / buyback /
  merger arb regardless of company. NOT hardcoded per-company data.

POST-EVENT PLAYBOOK — universal J-curve (Day 1 → Month 36+, Purdue 36-year
  study) + HOLD signals + SELL signals + post-tender unaccepted-share
  guidance. Universal pattern recognition rules.

ACCEPTANCE / DEAL MATH — interactive calculators:
  - Indian Tender Buyback: edit any input (total shares, buyback shares,
    promoter stake %, promoter tender %, public tender %, prices, position
    sizes, months to complete) → live recompute small vs large holder
    acceptance, premium captured, return %, annualised. Pure formulae.
  - Floating Deal: edit cash%/stock-shares-per-target/acquirer-CMP/
    target-CMP → live recompute effective consideration, spread,
    break-even acquirer price.

DISCOVER — raw RSS scanner with source-health diagnostics. Same data as
  All Situations but unfiltered (no tiering), grouped by category (SPIN /
  MA / TURN / CAP), with green/red source-health pills at the bottom so
  user can see which RSS feeds pulled successfully.

Type-check clean. Page is now ~640 lines (was 1339).
